[Name] Elixir
[Summary] Elixir is a dynamic, functional language designed for building scalable and maintainable applications.
[Description] Elixir leverages the Erlang VM, known for running low-latency, distributed and fault-tolerant systems, while also being successfully used in web development, embedded software, data ingestion, and multimedia processing domains across a wide range of industries.
[License] Apache License Version 2.0
[Homepage] https://elixir-lang.org/
